-- BMW says U.S. car sales up 16 pct to 33,417 cars
-- 
-- Wed Jan 3, 2007 7:01pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/04/us-bmw-usa-idUSFAB01262520070104

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - German premium carmaker BMW's vehicle sales in the United States rose 16 percent year-on-year to an all-time monthly high of 33,417 units in December, the company said in a statement on Wednesday. 

 That brought 2006 U.S. sales for the BMW Group, which includes the BMW and Mini brands, to 313,603 vehicles, up 2 percent over 2005's. BMW brand sales rose 17 percent in December to 30,945 cars. Over the full year, they rose 3 percent to 274,432 vehicles.